trans-unit.source: Enumerates the elements of an <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.IRemoteArgumentDictionaryContract"></xref>.

To get an IRemoteArgumentDictionaryEnumeratorContract, use the <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.IRemoteArgumentDictionaryContract.GetEnumeratorContract%2A> method of an <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.IRemoteArgumentDictionaryContract>.
Returns the key and the value of the current <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.IRemoteArgumentDictionaryContract"></xref> entry.

After an enumerator is created or after the <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.IRemoteArgumentEnumeratorContract.Reset%2A> method is called, the <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.IRemoteArgumentEnumeratorContract.MoveNext%2A> method must be called to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before calling the GetEntry method; otherwise, the return value of GetEntry is undefined.

GetEntry also throws an exception if the last call to <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.IRemoteArgumentEnumeratorContract.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, which indicates the end of the collection.

GetEntry does not move the position of the enumerator, and consecutive calls to GetEntry return the same object until either <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.IRemoteArgumentEnumeratorContract.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.IRemoteArgumentEnumeratorContract.Reset%2A> is called.

A <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.RemoteArgumentDictionaryEntry"></xref> that contains the key and the value of the current <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.IRemoteArgumentDictionaryContract"></xref> entry.

The <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.IRemoteArgumentDictionaryEnumeratorContract"></xref> is positioned before the first entry of the <xref href="System.AddIn.Contract.Collections.IRemoteArgumentDictionaryContract"></xref> or after the last entry.
